{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure mode: environment/external-system + module handoff error (embedding provider/model dimension does not match index dimension). Required setup: call the real embedding endpoint configured in production and compare returned vector length to real index schema. Mocked embedding responses can hide provider/model-dimension drift. Higher-level rejection: Agentic rejected because this check is deterministic shape validation, not model-judgment quality; behavior text is about dimensionality, not semantic correctness.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end API test against a real embedding service and real vector index metadata: submit a fixed query, capture embedding length, read index dimension, and assert exact match. Fail if mismatch or if API accepts mismatched vectors.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"System is required because the real failure can come from external model/index configuration drift that in-process mocks would mask.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode: module wiring/logic error at retrieval boundary (query vector -> vector DB/search adapter -> ordering contract). Required setup: wire embedding output (can be fixed test vector), vector store, and search adapter together with seeded fixtures; assert returned scores are strictly descending. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess is required, no AI-quality dependence, no multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Seed a local test vector index with known vectors, run similarity search through repository/service stack, and verify returned ite