d because failure can be reproduced without real network/OS primitives; Agentic not required because behavior text specifies 'no close matches' (score-threshold policy), not subjective model-quality judgment; Workflow not applicable.","test_description":"Populate test index with items whose cosine similarity to query vector is below configured minimum relevance; execute query via service layer and assert empty results are returned (no fallback noisy items).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration is minimum because the defect is at module boundaries (search adapter + relevance filter), not a single pure function.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure mode: environment/external-system performance failure (network/API latency, runtime overhead, serialization, real service contention). Required setup: run the real HTTP API path with real infrastructure dependencies in a production-like environment and measure median latency distribution. Mocked dependencies hide true tail/median latency contributions. Higher-level rejection: Agentic/Workflow rejected because pass/fail criterion is timing, not model-output quality or multi-agent reasoning correctness.","test_description":"Execute a representative load test against the deployed API endpoint using real embedding/vector/LLM dependencies, collect end-to-end latencies, and assert p50 < 2.0s over the defined sample window.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"System is the minimum level since only real infrastructure exposes actual end-to-end latency behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.1}}]}
